Comments:
Spicy to the rest of the world (including other states in India) is equivalent to hot, atleast colloquially if not documented that way. It‚Äôs only in Bengal that we categorize spicy as mawshladar and hot as jhaal . Took me a while to get used to.

Also, I‚Äôve seen many Bengalis trying to school Brar on Bengali traditions, nomenclature, culture, etc. Personally, I feel we should show some gratitude and respect to a chef who is a punjabi from Lucknow (which means has enough culinary experience and options to boast of) and yet time and again upholds Bengali food in his channels to educate the rest of India whereas all we are capable of doing is nitpicking and finding faults with anyone trying to do a job (and not just talking about it). If we‚Äôre so touchy about correct representation perhaps we should make efforts to take that responsibility up instead of continually trying to pull down someone who has nothing to do with bong culture but contributes to its promotion all the time. Not attacking anyone personally, as a Bengali I‚Äôm sick of our inclination towards constantly find faults and criticising without getting anything done ourselves.

Comments:
something wonderful for all children...
As of late 2025, McDonald's in the UK and Ireland introduced special blank white "Draw How You Feel" Happy Meal boxes that open from the side to encourage children to use the packaging as a creative canvas. This initiative, in partnership with BBC Children in Need, aims to help kids express emotions through drawing, facilitating mental health conversations. 
Emotional Expression: The, blank,, side-opening boxes are designed to be,, used for, coloring,, helping children, express feelings, as research found 42% of kids find it hard to talk about emotions.
Design Change: The, traditional, top-opening, red, packaging was, replaced, to, provide, a larger, uninterrupted canvas for, children, to draw on.

Comments:
So funny story going through the McDonald‚Äôs drive-through today
I ordered a large Coke. My total came to $1.08 because of the sales tax.
I pulled to the window I give her one dollar and a dime. She then says sorry out of pennies have a good day and shut the window in my face.
Now I‚Äôm not cheap by any means and really in the grand scheme of things it‚Äôs only two pennies, but here‚Äôs the catch‚Ä¶.
I look on the window and I see the sign that explains due to a national penny shortage McDonald‚Äôs was going to institute a system of rounding so if you spent under five cents, they would round down for you and if you spent over five cents, they would round up meaning they would not give you your change if it included pennies.Ôøº
Well to me that‚Äôs kind of shady because if you do this to the millions of people that they serve around the United States, those pennies that they‚Äôre short are actually going to profit McDonald‚Äôs. And yes, it‚Äôll even out because they‚Äôll lose out on the money that they‚Äôre rounding down but only the people that spend under the five cents are gonna get that benefit everybody else it‚Äôs over the five cents is gonna lose money. And I can guarantee you that the way their menu is set up prices wise there‚Äôs gonna be a heck of a lot more rounding up than there is down. 
Now it‚Äôs not gonna add up to anything that could pay a bill for somebody because let‚Äôs be honest nobody‚Äôs eating McDonald‚Äôs enough to have that add up, but it does seem kind of shady that they can do something like that Ôøº especially when they‚Äôre the ones that set their pricing and can rig the system in their favor.
So I waved the girl back over to the window and she said ‚Äúcan I help you‚Äù and I said ‚Äúyes you can, here‚Äôs three cents now let me have my nickel‚Äù. So I sat there for three or four minutes waiting for her manager to come open the drawer so she could put in the extra pennies I gave her and give me my nice shiny nickel :-)ÔøºÔøº

The "Speed-Growth" Without Chemicals
‚ÄãTo keep food organic while scaling for billions, we use AI-managed environments rather than chemical stimulants.
‚ÄãHyper-Spectral Vertical Integration: AI sensors monitor the "biotype" of every plant. If a potato needs more nitrogen, the system doesn't spray a field; it releases a precise micro-dose of organic compost tea directly to that plant's roots.
‚ÄãBio-Control Robots: Instead of herbicides, we use laser-weeding robots. These machines use computer vision to identify weeds and incinerate them with light, leaving the organic crop untouched. No chemicals, just physics.
‚ÄãMicrobial Seed Coatings: We use "beneficial bacteria" to coat seeds. This science allows plants to grow 20% faster by making them super-efficient at absorbing natural soil nutrients, effectively "speeding up" nature without breaking organic rules.
‚Äã2. AI Butchery: The "Zero-Waste" Organic Model
‚ÄãIn an organic system, every animal is a massive investment of time and care. AI ensures we don't waste a single gram.
‚ÄãForce-Feedback De-Boning: Unlike 20th-century industrial saws that "shred," 2026 robotic butchers use haptic sensors to glide along the bone. This recovers 10‚Äì15% more high-quality muscle meat than traditional methods, which is what makes a $0.39 organic burger economically viable.
‚ÄãBlockchain Traceability: Since the system is vertically integrated, every Big Mac patty can be traced back to the specific organic pasture it came from. This isn't for marketing; it‚Äôs for biological accountability.

Hey McDonald's!! This isn't a compliant or issue for once.. I‚Äôm a fan of the brand (born in '97!), and I‚Äôve always been so inspired by your older locations especially the 1950s style. I‚Äôd love to see future store designs lean back into that classic Speedee Service look with the bright colors and neon. The modern buildings are very efficient, but I think people of all ages‚Äîincluding my generation‚Äîreally miss the personality and warmth of the original style. 

Lately going into McDonald's locations i rarely see any kids or families in them.

Corruption in Ethiopia is not merely the result of individual wrongdoing; it is also a systemic problem involving the former EPRDF government. This reality was publicly acknowledged through reports published in the government newspaper Addis Zemen on October 15, 2008, and November 24, 2008. Under the principle that ‚Äúthe law is the law,‚Äù corruption cases related to public matters should have been prosecuted by the Federal Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission. However, the commission itself was compromised, and prosecutorial authority was transferred to the Ministry of Justice. Four corruption investigation files were subsequently submitted to the Minister of Justice, yet these records have remained undisclosed. This situation was again reported to the Ethiopian public through Addis Zemen on June 18, 2017, and October 26, 2018.

Although certain corrupt individuals were dismissed from their positions in the name of national and public interest, I continued my struggle against corruption at great personal cost. To sustain this effort and to uphold the truth, I sold my private house in Hawassa City, despite the risks to my personal safety. Despite this, the office involved lost the legal dispute at every level, from the court of first instance to the Federal Supreme Court. The final ruling ordered that I be reinstated to my former position at Legal Service Level 17, Step 10.

Contrary to this binding court decision, the office acted in retaliation by reducing my rank to Level 4, Step 10. The court ruling was improperly altered through administrative correspondence. At the same time, the Minister of Justice‚Äîwho was associated with four corruption investigation files initially registered at Level 13‚Äîissued formal letters instructing the office to implement the court‚Äôs decision as ordered. Despite these repeated directives, the prosecutor revoked the minister‚Äôs order and instead initiated a criminal investigation against those who violated the court ruling and undermined legal protection.

An investigation report was prepared by the Federal Police under the authority of the Director of Corruption Crimes Investigation, Ato Zelalem, dated 20/11/2013 and referenced under Order No. T/A/2/5X1/302/14. This report was submitted to the Federal Police Commission and forwarded to the Ministry of Justice. Nevertheless, corrupt officials within the Ministry of Justice continued to obstruct justice in secrecy. Although I repeatedly submitted evidence to the relevant government bodies, the rule of law in Ethiopia was violated in my case.

Based on the evidence available, I have suffered serious harm as a result of these violations, including significant damage to my health, which has left me unable to work. I therefore appeal to all honest and justice-loving people around the world to assist me in my pursuit of truth and justice.

Comments: McDonald‚Äôs used to be more than a fast‚Äëfood stop ‚Äî it was an experience filled with color, characters, excitement, and childhood magic. Over the years, the bright reds and yellows faded into gray walls, the PlayPlaces shrank or disappeared, and the buildings slowly turned into office‚Äëstyle boxes that don‚Äôt feel like McDonald‚Äôs anymore. People miss the old McDonald‚Äôs ‚Äî the glowing golden arches, the fun atmosphere, the characters like Ronald McDonald, Grimace, Birdie, and the Hamburglar, and the PlayPlaces that felt like mini amusement parks. To revive McDonald‚Äôs, we need to bring back the identity that made it iconic in the first place. That starts with restoring the classic golden arches, not the small ones on a pole, but the big, bright arches rising from the roof with Ronald McDonald centered proudly above the main sign. LED lighting can bring back the classic red, yellow, and white glow, making the building stand out again and feel alive at night. The PlayPlace needs a comeback too ‚Äî not the old unsafe structures, but a modern, safe, exciting version with LED tunnels, interactive climbing areas, character‚Äëthemed zones, and fun kids‚Äô music. Families would stay longer, visit more often, and actually enjoy the experience again. The building itself needs to feel like McDonald‚Äôs, not a corporate waiting room. Bring back the warm colors, retro‚Äëinspired rooflines, character murals, and fun seating that makes the restaurant feel inviting and full of personality. LED lighting inside and outside can recreate the classic atmosphere while keeping everything modern and energy‚Äëefficient. Most importantly, McDonald‚Äôs needs to be fun again. It used to be a place where families made memories ‚Äî birthday parties, Happy Meals, PlayPlace adventures, and late‚Äënight stops under the glowing arches. The path forward isn‚Äôt about reinventing McDonald‚Äôs; it‚Äôs about remembering what made it special. Bring back the magic, the characters, the colors, the excitement, and the joy. Bring back the McDonald‚Äôs everyone grew up loving ‚Äî but updated with modern safety, modern technology, and modern lighting. That‚Äôs how you revive McDonald‚Äôs and make it a true family destination again.

Comments: What A LOT of people don't understand about this promotion is almost every other order there would be 3+(three or more) of these meals per order and most of our restaurants were moving, practically, non-stop from 10:30a.m. until we close at 11 (12 on weekends), SO that makes it difficult to keep up with the demand. Learn the facts before openning your mouth; these were actually brought over to the US from the Australian stores and was just the excess that they couldn't sell over there, anymore. With all these fat fu(KS out here ordering as many as they did and upgrading their children's Happy Meals to these Grinch Meals, it no surprise that we'd have run out. Seriously though, within the first day, the Marshfield, WI store sold over 1000 of these, easily. So maybe keep that in mind when you're b¬°tching about not getting one. We, as employees, are also sick of hearing customers complaining about not getting one because here's a thought: maybe don't procrastinate next time you go for a specific promotional meal, huh? Besides, there's always next winter's Adult Happy Meals for all you big, dumb, -tism having, adult-sized children.
